						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa (?), Tribhuvanavīradeva (Kulōttuṅga III), Year 4 = 1182 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Mentions the gift of money (1 <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> and 4 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> each) for offerings by three individuals, that is, two woman of <hi rend="italic">Veḷḷāḷan Paḍaittalaikaḷ</hi> clan of Vijayamaṅgalam and a merchant of Kāngayam in Kāngayanāḍu.</p>						

